title.narrative: STRENGHTENED ENABLING ENVIRONMENT FOR RMNCAH

description.narrative: The health system has a strengthened enabling environment for RMNCAH., which contributes to Child Health, Child Health (Covid), Health And Emergencies, Health Systems Strengthening, Maternal And Newborn Health, Treatment And Care Of Children Living With Hiv. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Evaluations, Research And Data, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: Effective coverage of high-impact reproductive, maternal, neonatal, child and adolescent health (RMNCAH) interventions

description.narrative: The government of the Republic of Tanzania, Ministry of Health revised its subnational health sector planning guidelines to adopt Evidence Based Planning and Budgeting (EBPB) focused on equity and promoting use of data for prioritization and decision making. The new national CHW operation guide was finalized with its launch imminent. The Sector Wide Approach (SWAP) for partner coordination was strengthened. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:31/12/2019
